    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2466545">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2466545">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2466545)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2466545">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2156983&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250840" alt="psul" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2156983)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;" >psul</a></span> <span class="odate time_1456949592 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Mar 2016 20:13</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2466545">
									

<p>I like the fact that the OP/Oneiroverse is starting to come together a bit - the dream logic is still there, but there are characters now, and some basic rules are evident.</p>
<p>There were a few things here that I took multiple reads to work out - who the non-quotation mark voice belonged to, and why Ham knew about the Foundation. And I think the writing was a little rough at the start (just some mildly jarring things like using the names in the first two pieces of speech, ending sentences with prepositions, lots of adverbs and phrases like &quot;content confusion&quot;) but it came together more as the story went on.</p>
<p>A minor point - I suggest listing this ahead of Black Lotus on the contest page, as it appears to occur chronologically before that story.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Some&nbsp;possible&nbsp;typos</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;collapse</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>A general comment is that lots of quotation mark text ends with a period when it should be a comma, or the &quot;he said&quot; part starts with a capital when it doesn't need to.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>and had empty gauges in his ears</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I don't think this is a typo - I just don't understand it. What sort of gauges fit in someone's ears?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>prison chique tattoos</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Should that be &quot;prison chic&quot; or &quot;prison clique&quot;?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>He had to leave..</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Extra period, or one short of an ellipsis?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Bob bit his knuckle, drawing blood</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I have absolutely no idea who Bob is. Is that Urooj?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>He pointed at Jeremy, so as to show her through the wall.<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>”</strong></span> I couldn’t find Jeremy.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I think the quotation mark there should be an opening quotation mark before &quot;I couldn't find Jeremy.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>She pointed her palm purposely</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Can one point a palm? And should that be &quot;purposefully&quot;.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Police, open up.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The last action we read outside the dream was Sherry opening the door, which makes it strange that it's now shut again.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I get off work in one hour..</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Apart from the double period, I don't understand why the sheriff is saying this.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Ah! The enigmatic SCP Foundation!</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This sounds like a realisation on Ham's part, but I can't see what in the preceding discussion leads him to this conclusion.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“Actually,” Said the doctor, adjusting his glasses.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Because the tale to this point has been substantially from Sherry / Urooj's third-person POV, I interpreted the adjustment of the glasses as something that Sherry could see. Which meant I was very confused by the rest of the tale, until I re-read it and realised that Sherry and Ham are in the same room, and Dr Glass is not (albeit I'm not sure why one would do an interview like that).</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

