			<div class="content" id="post-content-2476511">
									

<p>I initially thought the beginning was a dream, because while that scene might have made sense in 1816, in 2016 having an unconscious person as a sort of side-show display wouldn't go over so well. It was incredibly confusing to understand what was going on even in the non-dream parts. I don't mind the dream-parts being somewhat incoherent &#8212; it goes with the territory &#8212; but that just makes it all the more important that the waking parts be clear.</p>

